# Page Composition Standards

Every page in this app follows a consistent composition pattern. These rules are non-negotiable when building or modifying any page.

## Rule 1: Design System First

Never build custom UI when a component exists in `src/components/ui/`. Before writing any inline `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, drag-and-drop zone, card, dialog, or similar element, check the design system.

Key components to reach for:

| Need | Component | Import path |
| ---- | --------- | ----------- |
| Actions | `Button`, `LinkButton`, `DropdownButton` | `@/components/ui/button`, etc. |
| Text input | `Input`, `InputContainer`, `InputIcon` | `@/components/ui/input` |
| Search field | `InputContainer` + `InputIcon` (Search icon) + `Input` | `@/components/ui/input` |
| Long text | `Textarea`, `AiTextarea` | `@/components/ui/textarea`, etc. |
| Selection (single) | `Select`, `RadioGroup`, `RadioCard`, `RadioSegmented` | `@/components/ui/select`, etc. |
| Selection (multi) | `Checkbox`, `CheckboxGroup`, `CheckboxCard` | `@/components/ui/checkbox`, etc. |
| Tabs / filters | `Tabs`, `TabsList` (variants: `default`, `line`, `pill`, `filter`), `TabsTrigger` | `@/components/ui/tabs` |
| File upload | `FileUploadArea` (drag-and-drop), `FileUploadCard` (uploaded file row) | `@/components/ui/file-upload-area`, etc. |
| Avatar upload | `AvatarUpload` | `@/components/ui/avatar-upload` |
| Cards / surfaces | `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardContent` | `@/components/ui/card` |
| Tables | `Table` + header/slot cells | `@/components/ui/table` |
| Pagination | `Paginator` | `@/components/ui/paginator` |
| Empty states | `EmptyState` | `@/components/ui/empty-state` |
| Dialogs / modals | `Dialog`, `AlertDialog`, `Sheet` | `@/components/ui/dialog`, etc. |
| Labels / hints | `Label`, `InputCaption`, `InlineTip` | `@/components/ui/label`, etc. |
| Date picking | `DatePicker`, `DateRangePicker`, `Calendar` | `@/components/ui/date-picker`, etc. |
| Badges / tags | `Badge` | `@/components/ui/badge` |
| Menus | `DropdownMenu` | `@/components/ui/dropdown-menu` |
| Tooltips | `Tooltip` | `@/components/ui/tooltip` |
| Progress | `Progress`, `Skeleton` | `@/components/ui/progress`, etc. |
| Stepper / wizard | `StepperHorizontal`, `StepperVertical` | `@/components/ui/stepper-*` |
| Toggle | `Switch`, `ToggleSwitch` | `@/components/ui/switch`, etc. |

If the exact component doesn't exist, check for a close match before building from scratch. When no suitable primitive exists, build the new component *inside* `src/components/ui/` so it becomes part of the design system for reuse.

## Rule 2: Standard Page Skeleton

Every page follows a three-layer structure. Do not deviate.

```tsx
{/* Layer 1: Outer wrapper — flex column, overflow-hidden, pt-6 gap below avatar bar */}
<div className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden pt-6">

  {/* Layer 2: TopBar — already carries px-8 internally */}
  <TopBar title="Page Title" right={<Button size="header">Action</Button>} />

  {/* Layer 3: Scrollable body — px-8 for 32px left padding, pt-6 gap below TopBar */}
  <div className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col gap-6 overflow-auto px-8 pb-8 pt-6">
    {/* Page content goes here */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Layer-by-layer rules

1. **Outer wrapper** — `flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden pt-6`
   - `pt-6` (24 px) is the gap between the avatar bar and the TopBar. Never change this.
   - `overflow-hidden` prevents the page from scrolling at this level.

2. **TopBar** — Use `<TopBar />` from `@/components/app/top-bar`. It already has `px-8`.
   - Pass `title` (required), optional `subtitle`, optional `breadcrumbs`, and optional `right` (action buttons).
   - Action buttons in `right` use `size="header"`.

3. **Scrollable body** — `flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col gap-6 overflow-auto px-8 pb-8 pt-6`
   - `px-8` (32 px) horizontal padding — left-aligned content.
   - `pt-6` (24 px) spacing below the TopBar.
   - `pb-8` or `pb-10` bottom padding for scroll breathing room.
   - `gap-6` (24 px) vertical rhythm between top-level content sections.
   - Use `overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden` if horizontal overflow needs to be suppressed.

## Rule 3: Content Hierarchy and Surfaces

Page content uses two surface levels: **background** and **card**.

### Background level (directly in the scrollable body)
These elements sit on the page background without a card wrapper:
- **Tabs / filter bars** — `<Tabs>` with `<TabsList variant="filter">` or other variants
- **Search inputs** (when standalone, not inside a card)
- **Section headings**

### Card level (white container)
Rich interactive content goes inside a card surface:
- **File upload areas** (`FileUploadArea`)
- **Asset grids / data grids**
- **Forms and form sections**
- **Detail panels / sidebars** (use `Card` component)

Card surface classes: `rounded-md border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm`

Corner radius must match the `Card` component (`rounded-md`). Do not use `rounded-xl` or `rounded-lg` for card-level containers.

Sidebar detail panels use the `Card` component directly (it already provides the white surface).

### Layout pattern with card surface

```tsx
{/* Tabs on background */}
<Tabs value={tab} onValueChange={setTab}>
  <TabsList variant="filter">
    <TabsTrigger value="all">All</TabsTrigger>
    <TabsTrigger value="photos">Photos</TabsTrigger>
  </TabsList>
</Tabs>

{/* Content in white card container */}
<div className="flex flex-col gap-6 lg:flex-row">
  <div className="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-6 rounded-md border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
    {/* FileUploadArea, grids, forms, etc. */}
  </div>
  <div className="w-full shrink-0 lg:w-80">
    <Card className="sticky top-6">
      {/* Sidebar details */}
    </Card>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Rule 4: Left-Aligned, No Centering

Content fills the available width and is left-aligned by default. Do **not** add `mx-auto` or `max-w-*` to center-constrain content unless the page explicitly requires a narrow centered layout (rare).

## Rule 5: Reference Pages

When unsure, match these canonical implementations:

- **List page with table:** `src/components/customers/customers-page.tsx`
- **Library page with filters + grid:** `src/components/templates/templates-page.tsx`
- **Upload + grid + sidebar:** `src/components/media/media-library-page.tsx`

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Every UI element uses a design system component from `src/components/ui/` (no custom buttons, inputs, selects, file pickers, etc.)
- [ ] Page uses the three-layer skeleton: outer wrapper (`pt-6`) → `TopBar` → scrollable body (`px-8 pt-6 pb-8 gap-6`)
- [ ] Horizontal padding is exactly 32 px (`px-8`) on the scrollable body
- [ ] Content is left-aligned (no `mx-auto` / `max-w-*` unless intentional)
- [ ] Tabs / filters sit on the page background, not inside a card
- [ ] Rich content (uploads, grids, forms) is inside a white card surface (`rounded-md` + `bg-card` + border)
- [ ] TopBar action buttons use `size="header"`
